obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (68098)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024&sectionId=68098&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Agriculturists' Loans Act, 1884; and Commencement.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on the first day of August, 1884.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (68099)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Local extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024&sectionId=68099&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) This section ^1*** extends to the whole of India except ^2[the territories which,`
  line `immediately before the 1st November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States].`
  line
  line `^3[(2) The rest of this Act extends in the first instance only to Uttar Pradesh, the Central Provinces,`
  line `Assam and Delhi and the territories which, immediately before the 1st November, 1956, were comprised`
  line `in the States of Bombay, Punjab and Ajmer.]`
  line
  line `(3) But any State Government may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette, extend`
  line `the rest of this Act to the whole or any part of ^4[the territories to which this Act extends] under its`
  line administration.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and figure "and Section 3" omitted by 2 A.L.O., 1956 (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line `2. Subs. by 2 A.L.O., 1956 (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line `3. Subs. by 2 A.L.O., 1956 (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line `4. Subs. by 2 A.L.O., 1956, for "the territories".`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (68100)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Repeal of Act X of 1879, and section 4 and 5 of Act XV of 1880.`
  content ^1[***]
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024&sectionId=68100&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Rep. by Act 1 of 1938, S. 2 and Sch. (w.e.f. 26-2-1938). Prior to repeal it read as:`
  line
  line `"3. Repeal of Act 10 of 1979, and Section 4 and 5 of Act 15 of 1880.--(1) On and from the day on which this Act comes`
  line `into force, the Northern India Takkavi Act (Act 10 of 1879), and Section 4 and 5 of Act 15 of 1880, shall, except as regards`
  line `the recovery of advances made before this Act comes into force and of the interest thereon, be repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) All rules made under those Acts shall be deemed ,to be made under this Act."`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (68101)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power for State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024&sectionId=68101&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government ^1[or, in a State for which`
  line `there is a Board of Revenue of Financial Commissioner, such Board or Financial Commissioner, subject to`
  line `the control of the State Government] may, from time to time, ^2*** make rules as to loans to be made to`
  line `owners and occupiers of arable land, for the relief of distress, the purchase of seed or cattle, or any other`
  line `purpose not specified in the Land Improvement Loans Act, 1883 (19 of 1883), but connected with`
  line `agricultural objects.`
  line
  line `(2) All such rules shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1914, Section 2 and Schedule, Part I.`
  line `2. The words "subject to the control of the G.G. in C." rep. by the Act 4 of 1914, Section 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (68102)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Recovery of loans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024&sectionId=68102&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every loan made in accordance with such rules, all interest (if any) chargeable`
  line `thereon, and costs (if any) incurred in making or recovering the same, shall, when they become due, be`
  line `recoverable from the person to whom the loan was made, or from any person who has become surety for the repayment thereof, as if they were arrears of land- revenue or costs incurred in recovering the same due`
  line `by the person to whom the loan was made or by his surety.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (68103)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Liability of joint-borrowers as among themselves.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024&sectionId=68103&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00098_188412_1663829667024
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `When a loan is made under this Act to the`
  line `members of a village community or to any other persons on such terms that all of them are jointly and`
  line `severally bound to the Government for the payment of the whole amount payable in respect thereof, and a`
  line `statement showing the portion of that amount which as among themselves each is bound to contribute is`
  line `entered upon the order granting the loan and is signed, marked, or sealed by each of them or his agent duly`
  line `authorized in this behalf and by the officer making the order, that statement shall be conclusive evidence`
  line `of the portion of that amount which as among themselves each of those persons is bound to contribute.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
